{{Quote|Move. Or you will be moved.|Ayo to [[Natasha Romanoff]]|Captain America: Civil War}}
'''Ayo''' is the General of the [[Dora Milaje]] tasked to guard the [[Golden Tribe]]. Ayo protected both [[T'Chaka]] and [[T'Challa]] throughout their rule, although she was forced to briefly follow [[Erik Killmonger]] when he had defeated T'Challa in [[Coronation of Erik Killmonger|ritual combat]], until T'Challa returned and defeated Killmonger. 

Once T'Challa regained the crown, Ayo helped [[Bucky Barnes]] free himself of his [[Hydra]] brainwashing. When the threat of [[Thanos]] had reached [[Wakanda]], Ayo took part in protecting her nation against this threat, fighting in the [[Battle of Wakanda]]. [[2024|Six years later]], Ayo was sent to take [[Baron Zemo]] into the custody of the Dora Milaje after Barnes facilitated his [[Liberation of Helmut Zemo|escape]].

[[2025|A year later]], following the passing of T'Challa, Ayo, and her partner [[Aneka]] worked together in the Dora Milaje at a [[Wakandan Outreach Center]], when mercenaries attempted to steal vibranium, defending [[Wakanda]] without the Black Panther. When [[Okoye]] was fired from position as General of the Dora Milaje, Ayo was appointed to General. Ayo, now General, was tasked with stopping Okoye from leaving Wakanda, when [[Talokan]] invaded. During the [[Attack on Birnin Zana|attack]], Ayo led a team to save the patrols, however Queen [[Ramonda]] passed away when attacked by [[Namor]], ending the fight.

Following a relocation of the Wakandans to [[Gorilla City]], Ayo witnessed the arrival of the new Black Panther, Princess [[Shuri]]. Ayo and the Dora Milaje would then [[Ambush on the Talokanil|fight]] against the [[Talokanil]] onboard the ''[[Sea Leopard]]'', until Shuri and Namor struck a truce. With the fighting over, Ayo returned to Wakanda and spent time with Aneka.

==Biography==
===Early Life===
Ayo was born in [[Wakanda]] as the granddaughter of [[Ala]].{{Ref|BPWFTCtD}} Growing up, she wanted to join the [[Dora Milaje]],{{Ref|MP101}} which her grandmother was part of.{{Ref|BPWFTCtD}} She chose to join the organization and trained hard to be able to fit in among their ranks.{{Ref|MP101}}

===Protecting T'Challa===
====Encounter with Black Widow====
{{Quote|[[Baron Zemo|Zemo]] [[Bombing of the Vienna International Centre|murdered]] our King [[T'Chaka]] at the [[Vienna International Centre|U.N.]] The man who chose us. Who chose me to protect him.|Ayo to [[Bucky Barnes]]|The Whole World Is Watching}}
[[File:CACW Ayo 3.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ayo threatens [[Black Widow|Natasha Romanoff]]]]
In [[2016]], Ayo traveled with King [[T'Chaka]] and Prince [[T'Challa]] to [[Vienna]], [[Austria]] to take part in the ratifying of the [[Sokovia Accords]]. However, she was absent during the time when T'Chaka was murdered. Distraught about what happened, she escorted T'Challa to his car when he learned from his [[Attaché]] that the [[Winter Soldier]] had escaped from the [[Joint Counter Terrorist Centre]] with the aid of [[Steve Rogers]]. They were stopped by [[Natasha Romanoff]], who wished to speak with T'Challa. Unwilling to allow him to be slowed down, Ayo stood up to Romanoff and demanded that she move aside, threatening to fight her if she refused. T'Challa, however, told Ayo to stand aside as he spoke with Romanoff who told him to side with [[Tony Stark]], so they could help him find and recapture the Winter Soldier.{{Ref|CACW}}

====[[Coronation of T'Challa]]====
[[File:Ayo, Ramonda & Shuri.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ayo awaiting the return of [[T'Challa|Black Panther]]]]
{{Quote|Take [[Nakia|her]] to the River Province to prepare her for the ceremony."<br>"Yes, General.|[[Okoye]] and Ayo|Black Panther (film)}}
Ayo was among the [[Dora Milaje]] who welcomed [[T'Challa]] when he returned to [[Wakanda]] from a mission to [[Rescue of Nakia|rescue]] [[Nakia]]. She stood beside Queen Mother [[Ramonda]] and Princess [[Shuri]] until [[Okoye]] asked her to take Nakia to the [[River Tribe]] so she could prepare for the incoming coronation ceremony.
[[File:The Dora Milaje.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ayo and [[Okoye]] attending the ceremony]]
Ayo then took part in the ceremony, dancing with the other Dora Milaje on the boat and knocking on the boat with her [[Vibranium Spear]] to activate the drainage systems of the [[Warrior Falls]]. Ayo stood next to Okoye during [[Zuri]]'s speech, pointing her spear at [[M'Baku]] when he menacingly approached Shuri. As M'Baku challenged T'Challa for the throne, Ayo remained by her general's side. When T'Challa defeated M'Baku, Ayo cheered with the rest of the Wakandans and chanted T'Challa's name.
[[File:T'Challa-Nakia-WalkingDownTheStreets.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ayo guarding both [[T'Challa]] and [[Nakia]]]]
Following the coronation, Ayo escorted him and [[Nakia]] through the streets of [[Birnin Zana]] as they took a walk together. Later, Ayo returned to the throne room when T'Challa was informed of the [[Robbery of the Museum of Great Britain]]. She then accompanied T'Challa to [[Shuri's Lab]] where he could acquire some equipment for his incoming mission.{{Ref|BP}}

====Erik Killmonger's Arrival====
[[File:BP EW 6.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ayo watches [[T'Challa]]'s duel against [[Erik Killmonger|N'Jadaka]]]]
{{Quote|Is there nothing that can be done?|Ayo to [[Okoye]]|Black Panther (film)}}
Ayo was present when [[Erik Killmonger]] was taken to the [[Citadel]]'s throne room. She stood behind Killmonger when [[T'Challa]] approached him in order to protect T'Challa should Killmonger try to attack him.

Later, Ayo and the rest of the [[Dora Milaje]] attended the duel between T'Challa and Killmonger, who claimed the throne of [[Wakanda]]. She watched as Killmonger slowly gained the upper hand over [[T'Challa]] and murdered [[Zuri]] who intervened in the fight. As Killmonger defeated T'Challa and openly mocked him, claiming he was unworthy of being King, Ayo asked Okoye whether the [[Dora Milaje]] could do something, but Okoye remained silent, knowing that they had to remain uninvolved in the fight.

Following Killmonger's victory, who threw T'Challa down the [[Warrior Falls]], Ayo was forced to give him the traditional Wakandan salute and to serve him. As such, Ayo stood in the throne room when Killmonger held his first [[Tribal Council]] and ordered the Wakandans to gather [[Vibranium]] weapons to be sent to the outer world.{{Ref|BP}}

====[[Battle of Mount Bashenga]]====
[[File:Black-panther-images-dora-milaje.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ayo chooses to rebel against [[Erik Killmonger]]]]
{{Quote|Ayo! The [[T'Challa|King]]!|[[Okoye]] to Ayo|Black Panther (film)}}
Ayo was with the rest of the [[Dora Milaje]] as [[Erik Killmonger]] and [[W'Kabi]] gathered [[Vibranium]] weapons and loaded three planes which would leave [[Wakanda]]. However, one of the planes was destroyed by [[T'Challa|Black Panther]], who had survived his duel with Killmonger. Like the rest of the Dora Milaje, Ayo was relieved to find out that T'Challa had survived. She also followed [[Okoye]] when she rebelled against Killmonger. Ayo was ordered to take several Dora with her to assist the King in her battle against the [[Border Tribe]] who charged at Black Panther.
[[File:BP Teaser Trailer 54.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ayo is soon cornered by the [[Border Tribe]]]]
For a time, Ayo successfully fought against the Border Tribe, avoiding the assaults of their war rhinoceros. However, she along with [[Shuri]], [[Nakia]] and Okoye were ultimately cornered by the Border Tribe, who ordered them to surrender. However, the [[Jabari Tribe]] joined the battle, enabling Ayo to resume the fight against their enemies. In the end, the Border Tribe surrendered.{{Ref|BP}}{{Clear}}

====T'Challa as King Again====
[[File:Black Panther5a8bb499d8c2f.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ayo joining [[T'Challa]] onto the [[United Nations]]]]
In the aftermath of the [[Battle of Mount Bashenga]], Ayo once again escorted King [[T'Challa]] and [[Nakia]] in the streets of [[Birnin Zana]]. Later, Ayo was among the [[Wakanda]]n delegation to journey to the [[United Nations]] meeting in [[Vienna]]. She stood behind [[T'Challa]] as he delivered a speech in which he declared that he would open Wakanda to the rest of the world and share their [[vibranium]] resources.{{Ref|BP}}

====Aiding Bucky Barnes====
[[File:Ayo TFATWS.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ayo recites the Winter Soldier activation words]]
{{Quote|It is time."<br>"You sure about this?"<br>"I won't let you hurt anyone.|Ayo and [[Bucky Barnes]]|The Whole World Is Watching}}
Ayo met with [[Bucky Barnes]] in [[Wakanda]], following [[Shuri]] removing the [[Hydra]] programming out of his brain. Ayo informed Barnes it was time to test if he was still susceptible to the programming, though Barnes was uncertain if they should try. However, Ayo assured him she would prevent him from hurting anyone.
[[File:Ayo.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ayo confirming that [[Bucky Barnes]] is free]]
Ayo then recited the activation words, and though Barnes was stressed upon hearing them, it confirmed he was freed of his brainwashing. After Ayo told him he was free, Barnes began to cry tears of joy at finally being free.{{Ref|TFaTWS104}}

====[[Battle of Wakanda]]====
[[File:T'Challa & the Dora Milaje.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ayo stands with [[T'Challa]] and the [[Dora Milaje]]]]
In [[2018]], Ayo was present with [[T'Challa]] and the Dora when members of the [[Avengers]] arrived in [[Birnin Zana]].  She, along with the others, went into the [[Wakanda Medical Center]] and soon witnessed the arrival of the [[Outrider Dropship|alien spaceship]]s.
[[File:Ayo fighting.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ayo fighting [[Corvus Glaive]]]]
She then stayed behind to protect [[Shuri]] while she worked on separating [[Vision]] from the [[Mind Stone]]. However, [[Corvus Glaive]], a member of the [[Black Order]], infiltrated the Center and attacked them. She fiercely tried to defend Shuri, but was swiftly defeated.{{Ref|AIW}}

===Assata's Achievements===
[[File:Assata Admires Dora.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ayo takes [[Assata]] to watch the [[Dora Milaje]]]]
As Ayo's cousin, [[Assata]], grew up admiring the [[Dora Milaje]], Ayo took Assata to watch them training alongside [[T'Challa]]. Assata looked on with awe, although turned down [[Okoye]]'s offer to train with a modified training regiment to accommodate Assata's disability. Assata chose to study science, and Ayo heard that [[Shuri]] had offered her a job as her assistant. Ayo got excited for her cousin.{{Ref|BPWFTCtD}}
{{Clear}}

===Hunting Baron Zemo===
====Reuniting with Bucky Barnes====
[[File:Ayo (The Falcon and the Winter Soldier).png|{{AltFloat}}|left|Ayo finding [[Bucky Barnes]]]]
{{Quote|Kukho into efuna ukuzaliseka ngaye."<ref>Translates from Xhosa to: "''There is something that needs to be fulfilled through him.''"; official translation: "''He's a means to an end.''"</ref><br>"Eight hours, White Wolf. Then we come for [[Helmut Zemo|him]].|[[Bucky Barnes]] and Ayo|The Whole World Is Watching}}
In [[2024]], upon hearing that [[Helmut Zemo]] had been broken out of his imprisonment, Ayo was sent to track him down. She went to [[Latvia]] where she left a trail of [[Kimoyo Beads]] for [[Bucky Barnes]] to follow. When he found her, Ayo demanded to know where Zemo was.{{Ref|TFaTWS103}}
[[File:Ayo and Bucky.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ayo making her deal with [[Bucky Barnes]]]]
Ayo asked Barnes why he freed Zemo recalling how she had let [[T'Chaka]] down by not being there to protect him from the [[Bombing of the Vienna International Centre|bombing]]. She then reluctantly told him he had eight hours with Zemo before they would come back to arrest him.{{Ref|TFaTWS104}}

====[[Skirmish in Helmut Zemo's Latvian Residence|Skirmish in Latvia]]====
[[File:Ayo meets U.S. Agent.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ayo being introduced to [[John Walker]]]]
{{Quote|Ayo, let's talk about this."<br>"[[Bast]] damn you, James.|[[Bucky Barnes]] and Ayo|The Whole World Is Watching}}
Eight hours later, Ayo and two [[Dora Milaje]] named [[Nomble]] and [[Yama]] arrived to arrest [[Helmut Zemo]], only to encounter [[John Walker]], immediately attempting to impale him with a spear. Walker challenged her telling her that they had no jurisdiction there, but Ayo retorted that the Dora Milaje don't require jurisdiction.
[[File:Ayo Dora Milaje.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ayo discovering that [[Helmut Zemo]] escaped]]
After Walker put his hand on her armor, Ayo swiftly threw him against a pole and began to fight against him and [[Battlestar]]. Shortly, [[Bucky Barnes]] and [[Sam Wilson]] tried to stop the Dora Milaje from fighting, causing Ayo to remove Barnes' [[Winter Soldier's Prosthetic Arm|vibranium arm]] and she expressed her disappointment with him. After finding out that Zemo escaped, Ayo told Yama to give Walker back the [[Captain America's Shield|shield]] and left with her and Nomble.{{Ref|TFaTWS104}}

====[[Arrest of Baron Zemo|Arresting Helmut Zemo]]====
[[File:Ayo & Bucky Barnes.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ayo talks with [[Bucky Barnes]] in [[Sokovia]]]]
{{Quote|[[Dora Milaje|We]] will take [[Baron Zemo|him]] to the [[Raft]]... where he will live out his days. It would be prudent to make yourself scarce in [[Wakanda]] for the time being, White Wolf.|Ayo to [[Bucky Barnes]]|Truth}}
Ayo, along with [[Nomble]] and [[Yama]], traveled to the [[Sokovian Memorial]] in [[Sokovia]] to arrest [[Helmut Zemo]] after being tipped off about his presence there by [[Bucky Barnes]].
[[File:Ayo in Sokovia.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ayo is asked by [[Bucky Barnes]] for a favor]]
As the [[Dora Milaje]] arrested Zemo and escorted him to the [[Royal Talon Fighter]], Ayo notified Barnes that they would be taking Zemo to the [[Raft]] and advised Barnes that he should make himself scarce in [[Wakanda]] as a result of recent events. Before she departed with the others, Barnes asked her for a favor for [[Sam Wilson]], to make him a new suit to be Captain America.{{Ref|TFaTWS105}}

===Losing T'Challa===
====T'Challa's Funeral====
Later, [[T'Challa]] revealed that he had been sick with an illness. Although everyone tried to help, T'Challa died soon after. Ayo attended his funeral and carried the casket off until a [[Royal Talon Fighter]] took it.{{Ref|BPWF}}

====Defending Queen Ramonda====
[[File:Ayo and Aneka.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ayo and [[Aneka]] at the [[Wakandan Outreach Center]] in [[Mali]]]]
{{Quote|I told you not to bring [[Vibranium Daggers|them]].|Ayo to [[Aneka]]|Black Panther: Wakanda Forever}}
[[2025|A year later]], Ayo, [[Okoye]], [[Yama]], and Ayo's lover, [[Aneka]], were posted at a [[Wakandan Outreach Center]]. Ayo, Yama, and Okoye stayed in a room while Aneka opened the door. The group stepped out and faced mercenaries who tried to steal the [[Vibranium]]. The group easily took down the mercenaries while Okoye argued with Aneka about her new [[Vibranium Daggers]]. Ayo gave Aneka a look of disappointment afterwards.
[[File:Ramonda and Dora Milaje UN.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ayo and the [[Dora Milaje]] with [[Ramonda]] face the [[United Nations]]]]
The next day, [[Ramonda]] faced the [[United Nations]] and told them that they were still a threat even without the Black Panther. She brought out the [[Dora Milaje]], who were holding the apperehended mercenaries. Ramonda used this to show the countries not to mess with them.{{Ref|BPWF}}

===Becoming General===
====Ramonda's Outburst====
Later, [[Ramonda]] called a meeting when [[Namor]] infiltrated [[Wakanda]]. They wanted to discuss how that could have happened. Ayo stood next to the Queen as [[M'Baku]] and [[Okoye]] argued. Ramonda then told them to stop. M'Baku wanted to kill Namor, but they were hesitant. Okoye then brought [[Shuri]] to [[Cambridge]] to get a [[Riri Williams|scientist]] that Namor wanted killed.

Okoye returned, failing to get Williams, leading to Shuri's capture. Ramonda fired Okoye from her position as general as well as the [[Dora Milaje]]. Okoye and Ramonda argued, but Ramonda had enough, yelling at Okoye, who left in tears. Ayo was appointed general of the Dora Milaje. She was fitted with the traditional gold armor that generals wore.{{Ref|BPWF}}

====Stopping Okoye====
[[File:Ayo at night.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ayo stops [[Okoye]] from leaving [[Wakanda]]]]
{{Quote|[[Okoye]], you trained [[Dora Milaje|us]], all of us. Do not make us spill your blood.|Ayo to [[Okoye]]|Black Panther: Wakanda Forever}}
Now the general, Ayo got word of [[Okoye]] trying to leave. She approached Okoye, who just wanted to get [[Shuri]] and make it right. Ayo tried to order her to stop, but Okoye kept walking. Ayo then called out her troops, who pointed spears at Okoye. Ayo respected Okoye and said she did not want her to be killed. Okoye gave herself up.{{Ref|BPWFDS}}

====Ramonda's Death====
{{Quote|General, plug your ears."<br>"Yes, my Queen.|[[Ramonda]] and Ayo|Black Panther: Wakanda Forever}}
Suddenly, [[Talokan]] invaded [[Wakanda]]. The [[Birnin Zana]] soon flooded. The [[Talokanil]] used hypnotic chants to lure the patrols overboard. Ayo, [[Yama]], and [[Nomble]] put on their ear plugs and charged at the patrols to save them. Yama threw an explosive into the water to kill the enemies. Ayo then got into a [[Royal Talon Fighter]] with Yama. They flew through the air and shot at Namor, who sliced the side of the ship, sending them crashing below. The fight ended with [[Ramonda]] dying, leading [[Shuri]] to become very distraught. Ayo attended Ramonda's funeral and carried out the casket, just as she did with [[T'Challa]].{{Ref|BPWF}}

====[[Ambush on the Talokanil]]====
[[File:Black Panther II Trailer (33).png|{{AltFloat}}|Ayo witnesses the arrival of the new [[Black Panther]]]]
{{Quote|May the ancestors save us if the [[Black Panther|Princess]] does not hurry."<br>"We may be going to join them."<br>"If so, hey, let us take as many of [[Talokanil Armed Forces|them]] as we can.|[[M'Baku]], Ayo, and [[Aneka]]|Black Panther: Wakanda Forever}}
The [[Wakanda]]ns were relocated to [[Gorilla City]] for the time being. Suddenly, a [[Black Panther]] landed in the cave. They removed their mask to reveal it was Shuri, who managed to recreate the [[Heart-Shaped Herb]]. Wakanda rejoiced with the new Black Panther. Lead by Shuri, they lured the [[Talokanil]] to a ship in the ocean called the ''[[Sea Leopard]]''.
[[File:Dora Milaje Royal Sea Leopard.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ayo and the [[Dora Milaje]] fight against [[Talokanil]] onboard the ''[[Sea Leopard]]'']]
The fight started and they climbed up the walls of the boat to kill the Talokanil, using ropes to get up and down. Suddenly, a ship thrown by [[Namor]] came crashing down on top of them. The [[Dora Milaje]] and Talokanil exchanged blows while the ship nearly tipped over. They soon became cornered, leading [[M'Baku]] to pray for protection from the ancestors. Ayo admitted they might be joining them soon. [[Aneka]] said that they might as well take some enemies with them. Finally, Shuri and Namor returned, having struck a truce, stopping the fighting.{{Ref|BPWF}}

===Peace in Wakanda===
====A New King====
[[File:Aneka and Ayo love.png|{{AltFloat}}|[[Aneka]] kisses Ayo in celebration]]
{{Quote|Thank you, my love|Ayo to [[Aneka]]|Black Panther: Wakanda Forever}}
With a newfound peace, Ayo and [[Aneka]] rejoiced at her home. Aneka kissed Ayo on the head and Ayo thanked her. Later, they prepared for the incoronation of [[Shuri]]. They did the ritual until Shuri was meant to arrive. However, she had left [[Wakanda]]. Instead, [[M'Baku]] arrived, challenging to become the King.{{Ref|BPWF}}

==Abilities==
<!-- The power list and levels has been carefully reviewed and approved with the media released as of Black Panther: Wakanda Forever. DO NOT MAKE arbitrary changes to them or it may lead to blocks. If something is wrong, please contact WikiProjects: Powers & Abilities -->
{{Quote|Hey, John, take it easy. You might wanna fight [[Winter Soldier|Bucky]] before you tangle with the [[Dora Milaje]].|[[Sam Wilson]] to [[John Walker]]|The Whole World Is Watching}}
*'''Master Martial Artist''': [[File:Ayo vs. U.S Agent.png|thumb|250px|Ayo fighting against [[John Walker]]]] As a member of the [[Dora Milaje]], Ayo received extensive combat training which allowed for excellent skill in many fields of combat. She is quite confident in her skills, confidently threatening [[Natasha Romanoff]] when she stood in [[T'Challa]]'s way despite her being an exceptional and famous fighter in her own right. During the [[Battle of Mount Bashenga]], Ayo defeated many warriors of the [[Border Tribe]] and survived uninjured. She even held off the stronger and highly trained assassin of Thanos [[Corvus Glaive]] and survived the fight despite being defeated. Her fighting skills were great enough to easily subdue [[John Walker]], a highly decorated U.S. veteran who was chosen to be the next Captain America, and even get the better of a reluctant [[Bucky Barnes]], disarming him by triggering the release mechanism for his [[Winter Soldier's Prosthetic Arm|bionic arm]], a feat Barnes didn’t know was possible. She also fought the genetically-superior [[Talokanil]].
*'''Spear Mastery''': As a member of the Dora Milaje, Ayo is extremely skilled at using her [[Vibranium Spear]] in close quarters combat and as a long ranged weapon. She was able to easily defeat many warriors of the [[Border Tribe]] during the [[Battle of Mount Bashenga]] and even fight off [[Corvus Glaive]] with it. She is also accurate in throwing it, being able to precisely throw her spear at a fellow Dora to wield. Ayo was able to wield another Dora Milaje's spear with equal skill to using her own, dominating John Walker completely into the defensive and would have killed him had Barnes not stopped her and subsequently effectively using the spear to push back Barnes, even hitting his prosthetic arm with the tip, though Barnes was holding back as he wanted to talk instead of fighting.
*'''Master Tactician''': Ayo is skilled at forming plans and leading the [[Dora Milaje]] when [[Okoye]] is not present. She ordered her warriors to attack [[John Walker]] and also lead the group when she guarded King [[T'Chaka]] and [[T'Challa]] at the [[Vienna International Centre]]. Once Okoye was demoted, Ayo became the leader of the Dora Milaje and led many strikes like the [[Attack on Birnin Zana]] and the [[Ambush on the Talokanil]].
*'''Multilingualism''': Ayo is fluent in her native Xhosa, as well as English and Russian.

==Equipment==
===Weapons===
*'''[[Vibranium Spear]]''': Ayo uses a specialized Vibranium spear capable of collapsing into a handle for concealment. Her spear along with others have been shown to be able to interact with technology by striking the ground with the blunt end, notably activating the drainage system for [[Warrior Falls]].

===Other Equipment===
*'''[[Kimoyo Beads]]''': Like many [[Wakanda]]ns, Ayo had Kimoyo Beads she could use as a communication device.
*'''[[Dora Milaje Armor]]''': Ayo wears the standard-issue uniform of the [[Dora Milaje]]. Later, when she became the General of the Dora Milaje, Ayo now wears a slightly more elaborated version of the Dora Milaje armor, notably with the epaulets, bracelets, and necklace being golden instead of silver. Being made of [[Vibranium]] weaves, the armor offers high durability and protection.

