==Trivia==
*In the comics, '''Ayo''' is a member of the Dora Milaje who fell in love with her fellow Dora Milaje [[Aneka]]. After Queen [[Ramonda]] sentenced Aneka to death for killing a rapist, Ayo stole two sets of prototype battle armor and rescued Aneka. Viewing [[T'Challa]] as absentee and unworthy king, Ayo and Aneka became the vigilantes known as the [[Midnight Angels]] and started a rebellion.
*In ''[[Captain America: Civil War]]'', Ayo was credited as "Security Chief."

==Behind the Scenes==
*Ayo's relationship with [[Aneka]] is believed by ''{{WPS|The Hollywood Reporter}}'' to have been the reason ''[[Black Panther: Wakanda Forever]]'' wasn't released in [[China]] due to the country's rules to not release films with LGBT relationships.<ref>[https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/black-panther-wakanda-forever-black-adam-china-release-1235260069/ ‘Black Panther: Wakanda Forever,’ ‘Black Adam’ Unlikely to Be Released in China (Exclusive)]</ref>
*[[Jénel Stevens]] was a stunt double for [[Florence Kasumba]] in the role of Ayo.

